                  </hi>. I am a leather-seller, and live in Church-lane, Whitechapel. On the 29th of May the prisoner came to buy some lea<lb></lb>ther—he had been twenty times before—he bought two pieces—they came to 11<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—while he was looking at the bin, I saw his hand <hi rend="italic">go</hi> to his pocket four times—he paid for what he had, and was going—he went to the step of the door—I said he had got some more—he said, "Have I?" I put my hand to his coat, and found two pieces; he then drew out two more himself—these are the four pieces—they are worth 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 3<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—I have one partner.</p>
